reviews.text: Looking for something different and found it. We got in and really didn't know what to expect. Found a table pretty quick in a little personal cove that gave some privacy for some good conversation. Hit the salad bar first, lots of good options and sadly was the high point. Hit the pizza next, and it was ok. Although they had many different pizza options, the pizza seemed to be subpar. Was too full for the pasta, but did try, but you have to have someone give you pasta, after waiting decided to hit the salad bar again. Finished off with the desert pizza, and it was kinda weird. Hiy the salad bar to get rid of the brown sugar with dough taste. The price point was pretty good making it a good spot for families.

Other than some of the pizzas being slightly on the extra greasy side, I absolutely love coming here. Great all you can eat for the price, with a great variety of pizzas, sides, desserts, pasta choices, and salad bar. They're great about checking tables and clearing plates. Definitely family friendly, my daughter loves it as well. They also have a back room for reservations.

Children two and under eat free. I love the salad bar, pasta bar, and dessert options the most.

Friendly staff and clean bathrooms.

Thank you for delicious food and great service!

Literally my favorite restaurant, and I‚Äôve been coming here for years. The food is always great and they keep the same best items while also adding a new one each month to spice things up. I love the seating too. I enjoy the privacy of the sectioned off little tables.

This is a great place to bring a family! We visited for the 1st time today. Super reasonably priced. The food was really decent, and eployees were very attentive. Even though we went at a very busy time on a Saturday, and the place was super clean. Definitely exceeded my expectations.

editorial_summary.overview: Lively, laid-back regional chain serving pizzas, pastas & salads, plus creative dessert pies.
